\'93All these things which God hates they do. And it is because of them that God has taken the Tabernacle of His Covenant away from us and has given it to the people who do His Will and His Law, and His Ordinance. He has turned His face from us and has made His face to shine upon them. He has despised us and has loved them. He has shown mercy to them and has blotted us out, because He has taken away the Tabernacle of His Covenant from us. For He has sworn an oath by Himself that He will not abrogate winter and summer, seed time and harvest, fruit and work, sun and moon, as long as Zion is on the earth, and that He will not in anger destroy heaven and earth, either by flood or fire, and that He will not wipe out man, and beast, and reptiles and creeping things, but will show mercy to the work of His hands, and will multiply His mercy on what He has formed. And when God takes away the Tabernacle of His Covenant He will destroy the heavens, and the earth, and all His work; and this day has God despised us and taken from us the Tabernacle of His Law.\'94 And while Solomon was saying these things he ceased not to weep, and the tears ran down his cheeks continually.\
And the Spirit of Prophecy answered and said to him, \'93Why are you thus sorrowful? For this has happened by the Will of God. And Zion has not been given to a foreigner, but to your firstborn son who shall sit upon the throne of David your Father. For God swore to David in truth, and He repents not, that of the fruit of his body He would make to sit upon his throne forever, in the Tabernacle of His Covenant, the Holy Zion. And I will set him above the kings of the earth, and his throne shall be like the days of heaven and like the ordinance of the moon forever{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://2411D6E9-F5D9-4588-8826-5909B8351609"}}{\fldrslt .}} And He who sits upon the throne of the Godhead in the heavens shall rule the living and the dead in the flesh forever. And angels and men shall serve Him, and every tongue shall praise Him, and every knee shall bow to Him in the abysses and in the rivers. Comfort yourself with this word, and get you back to your house, and let not your heart be wholly sad.\'94\
And the King was comforted by this word, and he said, \'93The Will of God be done, and not the will of man.\'94 And again the Angel of God appeared to him openly, and said to him, \'93As for yourself, you shall build the house of God, and it shall be glory and as a support for you; and if you will keep His Commandment and will not serve other gods you shall be beloved by God, even as David your father.\'94
